      "writtenOn": "2018-06-23T02:23:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As an interface, Watched seems redundant.  Watch implies a purpose, which makes sense when you look at it from the perspective of the scheduler.  These are the refs I\u0027m watching.\nBut the moment you export them, they stop making sense.  IE Milo doesn\u0027t watch any refs, it just has a set of refs that its interested in at the moment.\n\nI think \"Refs\" or \"RefSet\" is a better name of this interface.\nIn which case\nHasRef(ref string) bool\ncan just be\nIn(ref string) bool or Has(ref string)\n\n(At this point Refs is redundant the name of the interface would already imply they\u0027re refs).",
      "revId": "822047433ac333318e4121138b2ad6aca82115c5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
